76561198022043667,Recommended,416190,19810721,"Posted: 20 December, 2015",all,Jawsman01,"I LOVE this Sim!This sim delivers just what it claims to, and so much more. Which is a great deal more than I can say for ANY other simulator currently out or released in the last decade. Experienced Flight Simmers know what I mean here.This is the most fun with a Flight Sim I've enjoyed since BEFORE microsoft ruined the flight sim genre by dumping barely functional FS titles on the market. Look no further than microsoft's bottomless pit of greed forcing Combat Flight Simulator 3 and FSX onto the world knowing that barely anything less than a Cray supercomputer could run them above 16 fps when they were new and semi-new!I and hundreds of  thousands of other PC pilots wish that we had the months of our lives handed back to us that we ALL wasted in vain attempts surfing the web to discover some fix to tweak better framerates out of those rehash-cashgrabs.Can I get a witness?!Well not this Sim brother, this one looks good and runs  S M O O T H !This Sim does what it says AND MORE AAaaaannnd it's really FUN!Is it a fully dedicated  100% flight sim that is better than anything else ever created? No.Is it pretty close to that even though it doesn't brag that it is? YES!Is it better at flight simming than FS2004, FSX and Xplane?I honestly think so now and will answer that more confidently after the coming updates.> Vehicle Simulator is currently a better Flight Sim than 9 out of 10 titles in my opinion, and I played them all since the days of the Amiga 4K.Could it be better? Yes, and it is improving all the time now.It may not have the entire globe like FSX but what it does have looks and runs wonderfully.Pro's>Better at simulation than most other sims.>Small download, massive number of free DLC addons of very high quality.>Powerful physics that can be felt + High framerates maxed all settings with 50-75fps on midrange PC> Best described as crossing a physics based Flight & Sail Simulator with Gary's Mod <>Although a few crashes here and there due to my extreme and far fetched ideas in the sim I will call this a VERY stable simulator.> Love the music choices in game, especially sailingNotable features:Lots of options. If you can fly, drive or sail it then it can be done in here, and done well.* The community can make and import even more content  > EASILY <* What a treat to have some little known music {french and Mexican] playing in the background as you watch the sun set and stars pop out while sailing, yachting or in your one man sub! = Mucho relaxing...>>>> DROP DEAD GORGEOUS WAVES AND OCEAN [viewed from below or above] BETTER THAN ANY OTHER SIM <<<<* The air combat is on par with titles I spent far more for, and those titles never delivered.* Impressive and fun cockpit POV, although hoping for more polished graphics and sound variety soon.* The creator is excited and active to pick up were he left off pre-Steam, so lots of upgrades and content coming.One Example that impresses me:The in-game stock F86 jet looks like it is made from highly polished metal, almost chrome. Strikingly beutiful to look at. By contrast this is how DCS World advertises their $Extra$ charge F86 but theirs looks only grey in reality because their DCS engine is 20+ years old and cannot render shiny bare metals!* So this Vehicle Simulator DOES IT BETTER THAN DCS currently does! * [Yes I own all DCS]Sure the DCS cockpits are superior in graphical quality and function, but I see the Dev seriously upgrading cockpit detail, functionality and quality soon. Where DCS is maxed out being CPU greedy it looks to me that Vehicle Simulator is just getting started with lots of room to upgrade.☺ You cannot claim that from DCS or microsoft whose re-re-re-overhauled game engines stopped bearing fruit over a decade ago.Cons:>Wished I would have discovered this sooner.>Powerful simulator but I need tutorials to help me wring the most out of things. I am still confused on many aspects and stumbling around trying to figure things out.** Interface is VERY user friendly however.>The graphics are very beautiful at times, but dated at others. I look forward to smoother hard-dark shadows in the cockpits, sharper reflections, and other more modern graphical eye-candy that has spoiled us in other titles.>Sounds are limited with one plane or car sounding like the next.> Unknown at this time how to set up dogfights, create new vehicles, change textures due to lack of hand holding tutorials>Have to start Steam to play. Like most I want to be able to play offline since we live in such a bandwidth depleted areaMy hopes for the future are:* Be able to fly, sail or sub anywhere in the world* Updated and more modern graphics, textures, more realism rendering light and shadows and better explosions* Ability to set up player vs Ai opponents easier* More vehicles flooding the workshop <hint-hint>* More ocean life to sub around and sail by* More stock adventures, although there are more than most sims offer already* The ability to be an animal or fish or bird like in Gary's mod. [ this opens up the wonderful can of worms allowing the player to control [[create]] player animals like we create animatronic sharks for movies. ] Imagine getting to be a dinosaur, shark or whatever in this Sim, it'd be AWESOME!My respect and honest thanks to the developer and his family. So glad you came to Steam so I could find you!"
