76561197972244201,Recommended,416190,25162183,"Posted: 26 August, 2016",all,pebblegarden,"I've owned Vehicle Simulator for a few years, and over that time I've grown very fond of it. Lately I've been starting to use it as a way to teach my friends how to fly simulators, and so far it's working well in that capacity.Since most of those friends don't have joysticks or controllers, I've been learning to fly it with keyboard + mouse only in order to help them. The keyboard + mouse control in VS is surprisingly good, though helicopters are almost impossible to fly without a joystick.The game supports TrackIR and various peripherals.If you want a simulator that scratches many of the same itches as Microsoft Flight Sim or X-Plane without overwhelming complexity, Vehicle Simulator is worth a try."
,Recommended,416190,34762053,Posted: 5 September,all,martiniman_ala_cheese,"Vehicle Simulator is a great game that allows you to fly and drive a wide range of vehicles, including submarines, sailboats, aircraft, helicopters, cars, and RC quadcopters. The amount of DLC available for free on the internet for this game is vast, allowing for a wide range of scenarios on land, sea, or air.What I like:-Realistic sailboat controls, which I haven't seen in any other game.-Highly unique vehicles available like flying boats and spacecraft all in a single game.-Everything is customizable, and you can even design your own vehicles if you have the skill.What I don't like:-Although very difficult to get started with flying, once you get the hang of it, it's very fun.-The graphics leave much to be desired.-Many add-ons are from 3rd party sites, making me think twice about downloading a vehicle (although I haven't seen any malware yet.)This game is for vehicle enthusiasts who enjoy taking leisurely adventures, or designers who want to drive their creations with total control of the stats. I was tired of seeing high priced simulators with expensive DLC, so having a game with unlimited options and a one-time price was very appealing."
